Modifications

This is a modified (derivative) copy of a subset of the original FastHTML
library. The following changes have been made:

1. Server/Routing Components Removed (core.py):
   - FastHTML class (Starlette subclass) and all @patch methods removed
   - serve() function (uvicorn launcher) removed
   - APIRouter, RouteFuncs, HostRoute removed
   - Beforeware, Lifespan middleware removed
   - WebSocket support (_ws_endp, setup_ws, _send_ws, _wrap_ws) removed
   - Client (httpx test client) removed
   - StringConvertor patches, reg_re_param, StaticNoCache removed
   - add_sig_param, into, MiddlewareBase decorators removed
   - _wrap_call, _wrap_ex, _endp dispatching removed
   - signal_shutdown() removed
   - devtools_json removed

2. Server-dependent functions removed from xtend.py:
   - with_sid() (requires app routes)
   - robots_txt() (requires app routes)
   - sitemap_xml() / sitemap_url() (requires app routes)

3. Non-essential builders removed from xtend.py:
   - Socials() — OG/Twitter social card meta tags
   - YouTubeEmbed() — YouTube iframe embed

4. New Files Created (not part of original FastHTML):
   - starlette.py — minimal re-export shim for Starlette types
   - components.py — minimal ft_html/ft_hx + HTML tag factories
   - NOTICE — this file

5. Imports Cleaned (all files):
   - All `from xxx import *` wildcard imports replaced with explicit imports
   - common.py: removed imports of non-existent submodules
     (.starlette, .basics, .pico, .authmw, .live_reload, .toaster, .js, .fastapp)
   - core.py: removed unused imports (asyncio, contextlib, uvicorn, httpx,
     itsdangerous, fastcore.style, functools, anyio); added missing `import re`
   - xtend.py: removed unused imports (dataclass, asdict)

6. Type Annotations Fixed (all files):
   - Optional-call assertions added
   - `# type: ignore` annotations for Pylance false-positives
   - Return types corrected (Union, tuple, etc.)
   - Dynamic HTML tag generation block suppressed with pyright directive
   - LdJson return type widened to Union[FT, dict]

Files retained (modified):
  - common.py     — re-export facade
  - core.py       — HTML generation utilities (FT components, HTMX headers, form
                    parsing, response building, url helpers, cookies)
  - components.py — Minimal ft_html/ft_hx + all HTML tag factories
  - xtend.py      — HTML component builders (A, Form, Script, Style,
                    JSON-LD structured data, surreal.js helpers, etc.)
  - starlette.py  — Starlette type re-export shim

Files removed (vs original FastHTML):
  - All server/routing/middleware/websocket modules
  - live_reload.py, toaster.py, js.py, fastapp.py, authmw.py, pico.py, basics.py
  - IPython notebook sources

Purpose:
  This vendored copy is used solely for the HTML generation and component-building
  capabilities provided by the FT (FastTag) system. All server-side functionality
  (routing, middleware, websocket, lifespan, etc.) has been excised as it is
  handled by the ezweb framework's own server layer.
